  "prompt": "First winery in California?",
  "response": "The first winery in California is widely considered to be **Mission San Gabriel Arc\u00e1ngel**, established in 1771 by Spanish missionaries in what is now Los Angeles County. The missionaries planted vineyards and produced wine primarily for sacramental purposes, using a grape variety known as **Mission Grapes** (Vitis vinifera 'Mission'). \n\nHowever, the first commercial winery in California was **Buena Vista Winery**, founded in 1857 by Agoston Haraszthy in Sonoma. Haraszthy, often referred to as the \"Father of California Viticulture,\" played a pivotal role in developing the wine industry in the state by introducing European grape varieties and modern winemaking techniques. \n\nSo, while Mission San Gabriel Arc\u00e1ngel holds the title of the first winery, Buena Vista Winery marks the beginning of California's commercial wine industry.",
